@sethzenz
The reason extra packages were being loaded was that I had merged with 808patchX cmssw release.  I have now changed to 80X and fewer packages are checked out.
With the updated version of mplaner:egm_tnp_80x, it should check out exactly the same files/packages as with the previous version from matteo's area.

What's required to dump a variable into the tree is a simple member function in the Tag class.  That does not require that an extra member variable be used to store the information: the jets and the photons are all accessible through the tag already. A rough version of the needed function could look like:
float CosThetaStar() {
TLorentzVector jetl, jets, dijet, diphoton, vstar;
diphoton.SetPtEtaPhiE( diPhoton()->pt(), diPhoton()->eta(), diPhoton()->phi(), diPhoton()->energy());
jetl.SetPtEtaPhiE( leadingJet()->pt(), leadingJet()->eta(), leadingJet()->phi(), leadingJet()->energy() );
jets.SetPtEtaPhiE( subLeadingJet()->pt(), subLeadingJet()->eta(), subLeadingJet()->phi(), subLeadingJet()->energy() );
        dijet = jetl + jets;
        vstar = diphoton + dijet;

        diphoton.Boost( -vstar.BoostVector() );
        float costhetastar = -diphoton.CosTheta();
return costhetastar;

}
I guess in the end an extra variable would be ok too; this function is a bit more complicated than I had been thinking.

aah, ok I see what you mean. Yes in principle you can just dump all the required info and recalculate later in a simple macro. It is just so much more convenient if could just directly be dumped. Does changing the class def affect thing the code upstream ?
